properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 10 at 1:58PM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...COMPLEX WINTER STORM TO IMPACT THE REGION...

* WHAT...Heavy mixed precipitation of rain, snow, sleet, and
freezing rain expected. Through Saturday morning, 1 to 4 inches
of snow and up to a tenth of an inch of freezing rain is
expected. Freezing rain totals will be highest southeast of a
line from Darlington to Port Washington, with lower amounts near
Lake Michigan. The lower snow amounts will be to the southeast.

Additional moderate to heavy snow is expected Saturday
afternoon into Saturday night, with 4 to 7 inches possible.

Storm totals will be in the 4 to 10 inch range. In addition to
the snow, strong winds gusts of 35 to 45 mph will cause blowing
and drifting of the snow throughout much of the event. Gusts
could reach as high as 50 mph Saturday.

* WHERE...Roughly along and south of a line from Darlington to
Watertown to Port Washington.

* WHEN...From 7 PM this evening to 6 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Areas of blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty winds could
bring down tree branches.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Some freezing drizzle could occur Saturday
morning between the two rounds of precipitation.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM CST SUNDAY
